Priority: optional
Description: Gnome Window State Manager
 A CLI daemon that saves and restores window geometry (position, size,
 workspace, monitor) for GNOME Shell under Wayland.
 .
 GNOME does not natively remember window layouts across application launches.
 gwsm fills that gap by saving named profiles and automatically restoring
 windows as they open.
 .
 Requires the window-calls GNOME Shell extension to be installed and enabled.
